com.asemantics.rdfcoder.model.java
Interface JavaCodeHandler

All Superinterfaces:
BackTrackingSupport, CodeHandler, JavadocHandler, ParseHandler
All Known Implementing Classes:
JavaCodeHandlerDebugImpl, JavaCodeHandlerImpl, JStatistics.StatisticsJavaCodeHandler
public interface JavaCodeHandler
extends CodeHandler, JavadocHandler

This interface defines the Java Code Handler. A handler is responsible of receiving code analysis events and transform it in a usable format.

Author:
Michele Mostarda (michele.mostarda@gmail.com)

void startClass(JavaCodeModel.JModifier[] modifiers,
                JavaCodeModel.JVisibility visibility,
                Identifier pathToClass,
                Identifier extendedClass,
                Identifier[] implementedInterfaces)
Notifies the begin of a class parsing. The class is expected to be FULLY QUALIFIED.

Parameters:
modifiers - the class modifiers.
visibility - the class visibility level.
pathToClass - the path to the class.
extendedClass - the fully qualified pathToClass of the class extended by the starting class.
implementedInterfaces - the fully qualified names for the interfaces implemented by the starting class.

constructor

void constructor(JavaCodeModel.JModifier[] modifiers,
                 JavaCodeModel.JVisibility visibility,
                 int signatureHashCode,
                 String[] parameterNames,
                 JavaCodeModel.JType[] parameterTypes,
                 JavaCodeModel.ExceptionType[] exceptions)
Notifies the parsing of a constructor. The length of paramterSize and parameterNames is the same, the association between these elements is done positionally.

Parameters:
modifiers - the constructor modifiers.
visibility - the visibility level for the constructor.
signatureHashCode - the signature hash code.
parameterNames - the array of parameter names.
parameterTypes - the array of parameter types.
exceptions - exceptions raised by the constructor.

returnType - the return type of the method.
exceptions - exceptions raised by the method.
